abstract: A new policy adopted in the wake of a black man's fatal shooting by a white South Bend police officer calls for random inspections of officers' body camera footage and for officers to state a reason before they end a recording.
snippet: A new policy adopted in the wake of a black man's fatal shooting by a white South Bend police officer calls for random inspections of officers' body camera footage and for officers to state a reason before they end a recording.
lead_paragraph: SOUTH BEND, Ind. — A new policy adopted in the wake of a black man's fatal shooting by a white South Bend police officer calls for random inspections of officers' body camera footage and for officers to state a reason before they end a recording.
headline_main: South Bend OKs Random Inspections for Body Camera Footage
headline_print_headline: South Bend OKs Random Inspections for Body Camera Footage

abstract: The general manager of the company that operates McDonald's restaurants in Peru told local television that the beverage machine at the restaurant where two employees were fatally electrocuted last weekend had experienced an electrical fault but it was not reported to the company's maintenance department.
snippet: The general manager of the company that operates McDonald's restaurants in Peru told local television that the beverage machine at the restaurant where two employees were fatally electrocuted last weekend had experienced an electrical fault but it...
lead_paragraph: LIMA — The general manager of the company that operates McDonald's restaurants in Peru told local television that the beverage machine at the restaurant where two employees were fatally electrocuted last weekend had experienced an electrical fault but it was not reported to the company's maintenance department.
headline_main: Manager of McDonald's Franchise in Peru Says Faulty Drinks Machine Caused Deaths

abstract: New Year’s Eve gets noisy. But we all have our limits.
snippet: New Year’s Eve gets noisy. But we all have our limits.
lead_paragraph: Q: Last year, I had a New Year’s Eve party and my downstairs neighbors called the police. The party wasn’t wild, just 20 friends dancing and talking until pretty late. I don’t normally have loud parties, but it was New Year’s Eve! I want to have another one this year, but I’m worried my neighbor will call the police again. What can I do to appease them so the night goes better this year?

abstract: Iranian President Hassan Rouhani on Saturday welcomed Japan's decision not to join a U.S.-led naval mission in the Gulf and said he had discussions on ways of "breaking" U.S. sanctions on a trip to Tokyo.
snippet: Iranian President Hassan Rouhani on Saturday welcomed Japan's decision not to join a U.S.-led naval mission in the Gulf and said he had discussions on ways of "breaking" U.S. sanctions on a trip to Tokyo.
lead_paragraph: DUBAI — Iranian President Hassan Rouhani on Saturday welcomed Japan's decision not to join a U.S.-led naval mission in the Gulf and said he had discussions on ways of "breaking" U.S. sanctions on a trip to Tokyo.
headline_main: Iran's Rouhani Welcomes Japan Opt-Out of U.S.-Led Naval Mission in Gulf
headline_print_headline: Iran's Rouhani Welcomes Japan Opt-Out of U.S.-Led Naval Mission in Gulf

abstract: Business ties between former U.S. officials and an ex-Mexican security minister charged with taking bribes from a drug cartel have raised questions about what U.S. law enforcement knew about him before his arrest this month.
snippet: Business ties between former U.S. officials and an ex-Mexican security minister charged with taking bribes from a drug cartel have raised questions about what U.S. law enforcement knew about him before his arrest this month.
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY/WASHINGTON — Business ties between former U.S. officials and an ex-Mexican security minister charged with taking bribes from a drug cartel have raised questions about what U.S. law enforcement knew about him before his arrest this month.
headline_main: Work Ties Pose Questions Over U.S. Intel on Nabbed Mexican Drug Official
headline_print_headline: Work Ties Pose Questions Over U.S. Intel on Nabbed Mexican Drug Official
